owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

returns.desc: Descriptor of the set at the specified revision

params.data: Hash of external content (e.g. metadata or schema)

returns.active: True if all sets have a revision > 0

setURI(uint64).details: The returned template includes `{id}` and `{rev}` placeholders,      which clients should replace with the object ID and revision number      to construct the full object URI off-chain.

returns.uri: Template URI string for objects in the specified set

setURI(uint64,uint64,uint32).details: Substitutes `{id}` and `{rev}` in the sets URI template using the      provided object ID and revision.

returns.uri: Fully resolved URI string for the specified object revision

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

setContract(uint64).notice: Returns the contract address associated with a set

setDescriptor(uint64,uint32).notice: Returns the descriptor at a given revision

setOwner(uint64).notice: Returns the current owner of a set

setRevision(uint64,uint32).notice: Resolves and validates a specific revision

setSnapshot(uint64,uint32).notice: Returns descriptor and elements of a set at a specific revision

setSota(uint64).notice: Returns the latest descriptor and current owner

setStatus(uint64[]).notice: Checks whether all provided set IDs are active

setTouch().notice: Touches a set (increments revision without any changes)

setURI(uint64).notice: Returns the URI template for objects in the given set

setURI(uint64,uint64,uint32).notice: Returns the fully resolved URI for a specific object in a set

setUpdate(bytes32).notice: Updates the data hash of an existing set

setUpgrade(uint32,uint32).notice: Upgrades the kind or set revision
